<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1348,1806]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Remarks: While the specimens from 
<date box="[629,704,1529,1555]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" value="1087-01">I 1087</date>
are typical, those from 
<date box="[985,1060,1528,1555]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" value="1086-01">I 1086</date>
show the leathery, non-papillate integument 
<typeStatus box="[283,331,1565,1591]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
of populations previously attributed to 
<taxonomicName authority="(K. Viets, 1925)" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[768,1093,1564,1591]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceus">
<emphasis box="[768,907,1565,1591]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">A. coriaceus</emphasis>
(K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[955,1085,1564,1591]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="451 - 596" refId="ref78231" refString="Viets, K. (1925) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Hydracarinen aus Quellen Mitteleuropas. Zoologische Jahrbucher. Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere, 50 (4 - 6), 451 - 596." type="journal article" year="1925">Viets, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Molecular data do not support a separation of the two species (Blattner, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
